However, according to Brazilian researchers, the Amazon has the longest river system - according to these data, its length is 6992 kilometers, while the length of the Nile system is 6852 kilometers [7]. The area of ​​​​the Nile River basin is 3349 thousand km² [5] .The source is located in Rwanda, this is the Rukarara River, which flows into the Kagera River. The flow of water varies greatly and dramatically during the year.